Edwin, being very sad transferred m1, aka the mimic program the copied Fiona into a computer and made m2, the same endo skeleton that would copy David. (Cory Homage): 10:53 Coryâ€™s ending note sounds similar to him copying Hoppyâ€™s Hopscotch cutout poster JUUUUUU-â€œ scream  8. (FNaF Homage): 11:49 orange elephant costume resembles Orville Elephant from the Mediocre Melodies  9. (FNaF Homage): 11:58 gift box collectible gameplay from Security Breach  10. (Movie/Show Homage): 12:26 theme music for hedgehog cutout poster resembles the theme song "tra la la, tra la la" of The banana splits show which was a Hanna-Barbera show which was then turned into a horror movie with the unused script of the FNaF movie from Warner Bros.   11. 34:33
The game takes place in 1979, which sorta explains doing this all for $25. It's still, like, not a whole lot, but then again, Fazbear Entertainment has always been about giving such low quantities of money [$120 per week in 1992 for FNAF 1, $100.50 per week in 1987 for FNAF 2]. It appears we're always playing as characters who aren't doing very well financially in this series. I mean, Mike and Jeremy literally circle job applications on their newspapers as if to say "HOLY COW I HAVE A CHANCE!!" in the first two games, and Arnold is doing bad enough to be working with Fazbear Entertainment, so it makes a lot of sense. Also, Arnold didn't know about the Mimic. For all he knew, he just assumed it was going to be a simple "get in, grab it, get out" situation.

based on the search results, "Secret of the Mimic" is a Five Nights at Freddy's (FNAF) game centered around an animatronic called The Mimic. The Mimic was initially designed to care for Edwin Murray's son but became violent after Edwin's abusive behavior and the son's death. The game will be released on June 13th, 2025. It is believed that Jackie, the jester animatronic in the trailer, might be The Mimic in disguise, making her the first murderous robot seen.  btw edwin had a son it was to enterain his son

For context: This game takes place in 1979. Edwin Murray father of David Murray owns MCM where he and his team are commissioned to make costumes for other companies, one of them being fazbear entertainment. Edwin was so busy with work that he didn't have any time to watch over David so he creates a program called the Mimic to mimic David and play with David. The program works so good that he makes an updated version of it, mimic 02. This version was mass produced and almost ALL of his inventions uses this code. One day, David and mimic 01 were playing like normal until David's ball rolls into the road. Long story short David gets hit by a car and dies. Edwin, in GREIF, takes it out on mimic 01 and hits it basically destroys it. Since the mimic mimics it mimics the abusive behavior that Edwin did onto it. After Edwin "griefed with the mimic" he ran away (thats why he's missing) Now All of the physical and digital mimics are learning to hurt and kill. Fazbear entertainment being greedy tells a group of ppl to go into the factory and retrieve the schematics of the mimic and other things. Long story short the mimic kills them all and tears their limbs off. Another group was sent in. Same thing happened. Fazbear has now resorted to a singular person, less deaths, that is you. The events of the game play out then after fazbear entertainment uses the mimic and other MCM owned characters for their brand, aka the Monty look a like, the Mr. Hippo look a like, the Roxy reference, and even the music man. My name is Edwin. I made the mimic
Context: This game takes place before any of the games (1970's), set in Edwin Murray's facility. Edwin Murray in the books was tasked with turning the fabric suits from fall fest (a carnival owned by William Afton, into animatronics. Being an overworked father, he didn't have much time to spend time with his 4 year old son. So, he created the mimic. As stated in the office, it has the ability to  copy behaviors and personas of other people. However, one day, Edwins son got ran over by a car. But the mimic still copied the boys actions, making Edwin furious. In a fit of rage, he beat the mimic, tearing its body apart. But it survived, and now, it was copying Edwin's violent actions  against anyone it saw. Edwin disappeared, and fazbear entertainment went to collect what was theirs. The mimic was still at the facility though, and the people sent there were killed by it.

What is the gospel?  The good news that saves a person from the condemnation of hell is simply that Jesus Christ died for our sins, bleeding on a cross, then rising again from the dead three days later (1 Cor 15:3-4, Acts 10:36-43). He paid this ultimate price to offer you eternal life for free, not by your efforts or lifestyle reform.  What do I have to do in response to that good news to get saved?  There is only one thing we can and must do to be saved, and that is to believe in Christ (John 3:16-18).  Acts 16:31-32 â€¦Sirs, what must I do to be saved? And they said, Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and thou shalt be saved, and thy house.   If you believe in Christ just once, that he died and rose again to save you, then you have eternal life according to the Bible (John 6:47) and you cannot lose that salvation, no matter what (Rom 5:9, Eph 1:14, 4:30, John 3:18).    You must understand that to believe this good news, you cannot trust in your own works or good deeds as contributing even a small bit to your salvation. Do you believe that Jesus paid for all of your sins or that you also have to contribute? Either accept Godâ€™s free gift of saving grace and righteousness freely (rom 3:24, 5:14-18), or try to unsuccessfully work for it, but you cannot have it both ways (Rom 11:6).  Ephesians 2:8-9 8   For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:  9   Not of works, lest any man should boast.

However, to emphasize how hilarious I found this, I made a hyperbolic statement saying that I was dead because it implies that I found this video so funny I ceased to live. However, I am indeed alive and well so there is no need for you all to worry. I was simply employing the tactics c of figurative language in order to better and more effectively communicate my message. Additionally, using slang and sayings commonly employed by the youth has made my message more understandable and reachable by the younger generation, many of whom are in this chat. For example, I could have said "that video was a real knee slapper". This would have made sense to some of the older people in this chat as knee slapping used to be a sign of hilarity. However, in this digital age in which we now live, knee slapping is not as common and many of today's youth may not understand the reference. I therefore made my message more understandable to younger people through my use of simple, easily understood slang.
